","format":false,"excerpt":"Raja\u2019 ibn Haywah reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, knowledge only comes by learning and forbearance only comes by cultivating forbearance. Whoever aims for good will receive goodness and whoever seeks to evade evil will be protected from it.\u201d Source: Rawd\u0323at al-\u02bbUqala\u0304 100 Grade: Sahih\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24198,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/12\/18\/ilm-scholars-inheritors-prophets\/","url_meta":{"origin":35047,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Knowledge: Scholars are successors of prophets","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 18, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Darda reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe scholars are the successors of the prophets. Verily, the prophets do not pass on gold and silver coins, but rather they only impart knowledge.\u201d Source: Musnad al-Bazza\u0304r 10\/68 Grade: Salih (good) according to Al-Bazza\u0304r \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":43637,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2025\/05\/05\/abu-darda-learn-before-scholars-die\/","url_meta":{"origin":35047,"position":2},"title":"Abu Darda on Knowledge: Learn Islam before scholars die off","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 5, 2025","format":false,"excerpt":"Mu\u2019awiyah ibn Qurrah reported: Abu Darda, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cLearn sacred knowledge before it is taken away, for knowledge is taken away by the disappearance of the scholars. The scholar and the student surely have the same reward. Verily, there are only two kinds of men\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28842,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/08\/masters-knowledge-act-upon\/","url_meta":{"origin":35047,"position":3},"title":"Ibn Salam on &#8216;Ilm: Masters of knowledge act upon what they know","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydullah ibn Umar reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said to Abdullah ibn Salam, \u201cWho are the masters of knowledge?\u201d Abdullah said, \u201cThose who act upon what they know.\u201d Umar said, \u201cWhat nullifies knowledge in the hearts of men?\u201d Abdullah said, \u201cGreed.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Da\u0304rimi\u0304 595\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33999,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2020\/02\/16\/hasan-ilm-two-types\/","url_meta":{"origin":35047,"position":4},"title":"Hasan on \u2018Ilm: Knowledge is two types, beneficial or hypocritical","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 16, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Hisham reported: Al-Hasan al-Basri, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cKnowledge is two types: Knowledge in the heart is that which benefits. Knowledge on the tongue will be an indictment against the son of Adam.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Da\u0304rimi\u0304 376 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0647\u0650\u0634\u064e\u0627\u0645 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0652\u062d\u064e\u0633\u064e\u0646\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":21964,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/02\/18\/salaf-seeker-ilm-stop-learning\/","url_meta":{"origin":35047,"position":5},"title":"Salaf on Learning: Not befitting seeker of knowledge to stop learning","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"February 18, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Manadhir reported: I asked Abu 'Amr ibn al-Ala', may Allah have mercy on him, \u201cFor how long is it appropriate for a man to learn?\u201d Abu 'Amr said, \u201cIt is appropriate for him to learn his entire life.\u201d Sufyan ibn 'Uyaynah, may Allah have mercy on him, was asked,\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/35047","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}]